reviews.text: Went there today. The food was great and very delicious. The staff was also very friendly and polite. The food came after a reasonable time and they had a nice offer which made every second burger free (depends on day, they also have the same with pizza sometimes). All in all great experience, great food and great staff

We ordered a pizza, pasta, meatballs and drinks and everything was delicious, especially the meatballs, which are served in a rich tomato sauce with plenty of garlic.  Happy hour runs from 4-8pm and there are daily specials.  The staff were friendly and attentive. We'll be back!
I went with my HK local family and they loved the eats and dessert!  We had a fantastic experience with great service and delicious food! I highly recommend this restaurant.

I am a very fussy eater, and this place really surprised me, VERY tasty and fresh food!!! Freindly staff, many options...and lottsss of cocktails to choose from. Perfect for that western food fix....with some oriental choices to choose from too.
Have had great meals there on 2 occasions. Food has been excellent. Can recommend the bangers & mash, shepherds pie & apple crumble. Limited choice on alcohol at moment, but is a byo.

reviews.text: Great location however the service is suck. They haven't any amenities at the rooms... rooms and showers are too small.  The front desk staff are just there and they won't offer you any help

It’s a nice clean hotel, in walking distance to restaurants and the ferries.

The price is reasonable, which makes this a good choice if you don’t need extended amenities of a full hotel service.

Stayed here when visiting Hong Kong on a 4 day layover when travelling home to the UK from New Zealand.
The hotel was well situated and offered good sized standard rooms with all the facilities you would expect. Our room was high up in the building so offered great views across Hong Kong harbour.
Tram stop almost outside, train station not to far and easy walking to local shops and restaurants etc.
Recommended 👍

I have been staying at ibis at different hotels around the globe because their well priced and pretty decent. This is no exception, we had a leak in our room when we checked in and they upgraded us to a harbor view for rest of our stay. Really great

It's a good hotel, located quite near to the main central area in Hong Kong .
It's a 3star hotel...with small but good clean rooms .
U can really consider this hotel especially if you can try and get higher floor so that you can have a feel of the harbour view from your room.
Bathrooms are nice, and clean.
Breakfast menu is average.
Hotel staff is good though .

6월말 방문했습니다.
시티뷰로 예약했는데 빌딩 사이로 강가와 구룡반도쪽이 보여서 기분이 좋았습니다. 별다른 추가요금없이 얼리체크인을 해주셔서 감사했습니다.
직원들 모두 친절했으며 한국인 스탭이 있어서 좋습니다. 건물 1층에 스타벅스, 펍이 있어서 아침 저녁에 이용하기 좋습니다.
